## Phase 3: Complex Features

### 3. Line-Level Live Edit
#### [MODIFY] [EditorPane.jsx](file:///home/dtc/Desktop/SutraKnowledgeBase/client/src/components/EditorPane.jsx)
- Rewrite `LiveEditPane`: split content by `\n` (lines, not blocks)
- Only the currently editing line shows raw markdown; all others render as HTML
- On Enter → move to next line, previous line re-renders
- On click → switch that line to editing mode

### 2. Line-by-Line Scroll Sync
#### [MODIFY] [markdown.js](file:///home/dtc/Desktop/SutraKnowledgeBase/client/src/utils/markdown.js)
- Add `data-source-line` attributes to rendered HTML elements
#### [MODIFY] [EditorPane.jsx](file:///home/dtc/Desktop/SutraKnowledgeBase/client/src/components/EditorPane.jsx)
- Use source-line attributes to align editor cursor line with corresponding rendered element

### 15. Backup & Restore
#### [NEW] [backup.js](file:///home/dtc/Desktop/SutraKnowledgeBase/server/routes/backup.js)
- `GET /api/backup/download` — ZIP all user files + collection data
- `POST /api/backup/create` — Copy current DB with timestamp + userId
- `GET /api/backup/list` — List previous backups
- `POST /api/backup/restore/:id` — Auto-backup current, then restore selected backup
#### [MODIFY] [index.js](file:///home/dtc/Desktop/SutraKnowledgeBase/server/index.js)
- Register backup routes
#### [MODIFY] [client.js](file:///home/dtc/Desktop/SutraKnowledgeBase/client/src/api/client.js)
- Add backup API methods
#### [MODIFY] [SettingsModal.jsx](file:///home/dtc/Desktop/SutraKnowledgeBase/client/src/components/SettingsModal.jsx)
- Add "Backup" tab with download, backup, restore UI

